I would like to add a couple things to this post but I totally agree with
you David being a part of this family is pretty amazing it is not something
that can be explained either, i guess vws just attract the cool volks. First
of all David that is pretty impressive 3 yrs w/o drivin your bus, I must say
i prolly wouldn't have made it that far if not for drivin my bus b/c just
driving it and seein the smiles on ppls faces when they see the funny shaped
white toaster comin towards them proudly bearing the license plate  "PHAT
VW", and all the waves i get from motorists air cooled or not. Keep workin
David you think you love your bus now .......just wait :)

Secondly I would like to send a special thankyou to a specific list member
David Schwarze [sde(-at-)home.com]. The reason for this is recently I had been
lookin for a digital thermometer like the ones discussed in recent threads
on the list. I had absolutely no luck at all finding one in my city (230,000
ppl so not a small city) Then David posted about seein one at costco so i
raced to grab one only to find out that costco in canada doesn't sell the
same stuff as the U.S. So half expecting to be turned down I emailed David
Schwarze and asked him if he would mind picking one up for me and shipping
it to me, well this morning i recieved a package from texas and the
thermometer was exactly what i had been looking for.

So in closing David thank you VERY much for your time spent running around
helping me out. People like you are one of the reasons being a type 2 owner
is so enjoyable.

Scott Loucks
